{"questionId": "65833256", "correctAnswer": "A", "section": "Math", "steps": [{"title": "Solve the system by substitution", "content": "Substitute $y=6x+16$ into $-7x-y=36$: $$-7x-(6x+16)=36.$$ Simplify: $-13x=52$, so $x=-4$."}, {"title": "Find the matching ordered pair", "content": "Then $y=6(-4)+16=-8$. The answer is <strong>(A) $(-4,-8)$</strong>."}]}